author: maureenohare
title: New 'Star Wars' planes feature R2-D2 and BB-8
text:
CNN Leadership
New ANA 'Star Wars' planes feature R2-D2 and BB-8 Updated 1825 GMT (0125 HKT) August 18, 2015 7 photos: ANA reveals new 'Star Wars' planes To capitalize on the December premiere of "Star Wars: The Force Awakens," Japan carrier All Nippon Airways has launched a fleet of "Star Wars"-themed planes. Hide Caption 1 of 7 7 photos: ANA reveals new 'Star Wars' planes The airline debuted plans in April for the R2-D2 ANA jet, a Boeing 787-9 Dreamliner bearing the beloved droid's likeness. Hide Caption 2 of 7 7 photos: ANA reveals new 'Star Wars' planes The R2-D2 ANA jet is scheduled to go into service on international routes in the fall. Hide Caption 3 of 7 7 photos: ANA reveals new 'Star Wars' planes The new "Star Wars" ANA jet will feature R2-D2 on the outside of a Boeing 767-300 with BB-8, a new droid from "Star Wars: The Force Awakens." It is scheduled to start flying domestic Japanese routes in November. Hide Caption 4 of 7 7 photos: ANA reveals new 'Star Wars' planes The planes also will offer all six "Star Wars" films as part of its in-flight entertainment on international routes, the first time any "Star Wars" film has been part of in-flight entertainment. Hide Caption 5 of 7 7 photos: ANA reveals new 'Star Wars' planes Another vessel, a Boeing 777-300ER featuring the roly-poly BB-8, is scheduled to start serving international routes between Japan and North America in March. Hide Caption 6 of 7 7 photos: ANA reveals new 'Star Wars' planes The ANA "Star Wars" Project was announced in April, a partnership between the airline and Walt Disney. ANA was the launch customer for the 787, which entered service in 2011. Hide Caption
